./tools/lpn-lattice-sequence/README.md:3:This is a bounded, deterministic synthetic-control benchmark, **not** an OCTRA key-recovery claim. It writes compact JSON to `results/lpn-lattice-controls.json`; it records neither timings nor secret values.
./tools/lpn-lattice-sequence/README.md:17:Every algorithm reports its own work unit (`candidate_assignments_scored`, `information_sets_sampled`, `rows_in_square_system`, `row_combinations_tested`, or `lovasz_checks`). These units are intentionally not compared across methods. Short-dual output reports observed parity fraction but is explicitly labeled `dependency_enumeration_only`; it is not presented as recovered decoding information.
./tools/lpn-lattice-sequence/README.md:25:It then runs deterministic textbook LLL with exact rational Gram-Schmidt arithmetic and `delta=3/4`; no optional backend is required. The toy positive has a planted weight-two lattice vector (squared norm 2). Five seed-frozen matched negatives have no nonzero binary kernel and therefore shortest squared norm 4. Acceptance requires LLL to recover the planted vector, every lattice negative to remain at squared norm at least 4, and every independent-label decoder negative to exceed a 1/4 held-out error rate.
